Description: “The RNA concentration associated with a 50% probability of a positive culture was 7.8 x 10^5 for MTS and 5.2 x 10^6 for saliva (Figure S2).”
“Two (3%) of the 66 fine-aerosol samples collected from participants while wearing face masks were culture-positive”
“The other culture-positive aerosol sample was one of 98 aerosol samples below the 75-copy limit of detection for RNA”
“The quantity of viral RNA in the fine-aerosol fraction was 1.9-fold (95% CI 1.2 to 2.9-fold)”
“Days since start of symptoms or first positive test if asymptomatic or presymptomatic to first breath sample; 3 subjects reported no symptoms”
